The show, “The first temptation of Christ”, was created by Brazilian YouTuber, Porta dos Fundos and is on Netflix. JOHANNESBURG - Almost two million Brazilians have signed a petition to have a comedy show depicting Jesus as a gay man, cancelled. The first temptation of Christ was created by Brazilian YouTuber, Porta dos Fundos and is on Netflix. In the show, Jesus brings home his presumed boyfriend Orlando to meet the Holy Family. READ: 'Stranger Things' breaks Netflix viewing records An online petition on Change.org says the show is offensive. A local Catholic association has also unsuccessfully gone to court to seek an order to take down the programme. Dos Fundos, has defended himself saying he values artistic freedom and humour through satire.